ight on: Kay Faith}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019 ===\n{{Discography|Name=YoungstaCPT - 1000 Mistakes|Album=Things Take Time(3T)|Released=2019|from Album=THINGS.TAKE.TIME (3T)|Format=Digital Album}}<ref>{{Citation|title=YoungstaCPT (Ft. Robert Black) \u2013 1000 Mistakes|url=https://genius.com/Youngstacpt-1000-mistakes-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>{{Discography|Name=Sthino Le Thwenny  - Run|Released=2019}}<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.slikouronlife.co.za/blog/11914/castinothehero-x-thwennythwenny-run|title=Music: Castino The Hero x Thwenny Thwenny - Run|website=www.slikouronlife.co.za|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>{{Discography|Name=Zoocci Coke Dope with DieMondez - Rare|Album=Die Dope|Released=2019|from Album=Die Dope}}<ref name=\":2\">{{Citation|title=Zoocci Coke Dope (Ft. Die Mondez) \u2013 Rare Intro|url=https://genius.com/Zoocci-coke-dope-rare-intro-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>{{Discography|Name=Chad Da Don - Fede (featuring. FOCALISTIC)|Released=2019}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slikouronlife.co.za/blog/13737/at-chaddadon-ft-at-focalistic-at-venomzm-fede|title=Music: Chad Da Don ft Focalistic & Dj Venom - Fede|website=www.slikouronlife.co.za|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>{{Discography|Name=Manu Worldstar - Sheba|Album=Young African Story|Released=2019|from Album=Young African Story  (EP)}}<ref name=\":6\">{{Citation|title=Manu Worldstar \u2013 Sheba|url=https://genius.com/Manu-worldstar-sheba-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>{{Discography|Name=Chad Da Don - F.U. 2 (featuring. YoungstaCPT)|Released=2019}}<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.slikouronlife.co.za/blog/13242/at-chaddadon-ft-at-youngstacpt-fu2|title=Stream & Download: Chad Da Don ft YoungstaCpt -F U 2|website=www.slikouronlife.co.za|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:South African record producers]]\n[[Category:South African audio engineers]]\n[[Category:21st-century South African businesspeople]]\n", "text_old": "'''Edward Mohlomi Ramolula''' (born May 14, 1991), known professionally as '''AirDee''' is a South African record producer, audio engineer and entrepreneur. He is the founder of his proprietorship AirDee Global Production  under which he produces and distributes music for many of the artists he works with. Ramolula has produced charting songs for artists including [[Locnville]], [[L-Tido]], [[K.O (rapper)|K.O]], [[Cashtime]] and [[Chad (rapper)|Chad Da Don]] among others.{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = AirDee\n| image            = [[File:AirDee Pictured in 2019.jpg|thumb|AirDee Pictured in 2019]]\n| image_upright    = 0.9\n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n<!-- | image_size       = 259kb ... this strongly deprecated parameter is used as 200px (set width), x300px (set height), or 200x300px (max width & max height) ... see [[Template:Infobox person]] -->| alt              = Man standing against a wall. <!-- say who it is. See [[Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Accessibility/Alternative text for images#Importance of context]] for criticism of a bad alt text for a picture of [[Elizabeth II]]. -->\n| caption          = Ramolula in 2019\n| background       = non_performing_personnel\n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| birth_name       = Edward Mohlomi Ramolula\n| alias            = El Mucho\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1991|05|14}}\n| birth_place      = [[Bloemfontein, Free State]], South Africa\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Hip-Hop/Rap]]|[[Trap music|Trap]]|[[Electronic Music]]|}}\n| occupation       = [[Record Producer]], [[Instrumentalist]]\n| instrument       = {{hlist|[[Fl Studio]]|[[Keyboard instrument|Keyboards]]|[[Drum Machine]]|[[Propellerhead Reason]]|}}\n| years_active     = 2014\u2013present\n| label            = Cashtime (former), AirDee Global Production\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|DJ Vigilante|YoungstaCPT|[[Chad Da Don]]|[[Locnville]]|[[Cashtime]]|[[Nadia Nakai]] |Psyfo|Zoocci Coke Dope|Kid X|Focalistic}}|\n| module           = \n| module2          = \n| module3          = \n}}\nDuring the early 2010s Ramolula worked extensively with Psyfo producing a number of records notably 'Sorry Makhe' by DJ Vigilante and 'Imma Tell Her' by DJ Capital with the latter featuring Psyfo on the chorus. Ramolula is credited with production on [[IFani|iFani's]] Club 808 chart topping single 'Milli'. Most recently, in a bid to showcase his versatility Ramolula has been working with a lot of artists from other genre's. This has spawned the radio excitable single 'Better With Silence'<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.warnermusic.co.za/multi-platinum-electro-hop-duo-locnville-present-their-latest-single-better-with-silence/|title=Multi-Platinum electro-hop duo, Locnville present their latest single 'Better With Silence' {{!}} Warner Music South Africa|language=en-ZA|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> which has Ramolula as a lead artist alongside [[Locnville]] with additional vocals by YoungstaCPT.\n\n== Early life ==\nBorn in  the judicial capital of South Africa, Ramolula's musical journey started to take shape when he was 16. He would often participate in beat boxing and hip hop cypher battles with school mates. From thereon he cemented his identity with hip hop music's  versatility and its massive cultural influence of trends and the found his passion among  general consensus with the youth, music. His skill was honed during university days where he used breaks between classes to master his craft and technical ability. During this period of his life Ramolula decided that, despite studying Agriculture at the Central University of Technology he would yield the farms for the love of music, a SlikourOnLife article<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slikouronlife.co.za/blog/4878/a-sit-down-with-producer-extraordinaire-airedeeglobal-with-mshelen_n|title=A Sit Down With Producer Extraordinaire @AiredeeGlobal With @MsHelen_N|website=www.slikouronlife.co.za|language=en|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> on Ramolula states \"He doesn't miss the farm\", a sitdown interview in which the producer shares how he used to randomly send beats to Rappers until he got his break. How growing up in a musical home he knew he would end up in the record industry.\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2014 - 2016: ''Cashtime & Breakthrough hits'' ===\nRapper IFani met Ramolula through BlackBerry Messenger. They would subsequently work on 'Milli'. This song brought mainstream success for Ramolula after getting considerable airplay.Ramolula would then go on to work with Psyfo on the DJ Capital single 'Imma Tell Her'.<ref name=\":4\" /> It was during this period that Ramolula produced  'Sorry Makhe' by DJ Vigilante.<ref name=\":5\" /> Ramolula also had a brief stint as an in house record producer for Cashtime Life.\n[[File:Ramolula_in_studio_with_Chad.jpg|thumb|Ramolula (second from left) pictured with Kay Faith, Chad Da Don.]]\nRamolula won Best Producer at the Free State Golden Bean Awards<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.news24.com/SouthAfrica/Local/Express-News/golden-bean-pays-homage-to-fs-music-acts-20151110|title=Golden Bean pays homage to FS music acts|date=2015-11-11|website=News24|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> at the 2016 Ceremony.\n\n=== 2017 - 2019: ''AirDee Global Production and Electronic Sound'' ===\nIn 2017 Ramolula was named in the list of \"9 Producers behind South African Hip Hop Hits by Live Mag\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livemag.co.za/9-young-south-african-producers-behind-your-favourite-hip-hop-hits/|title=9 young South African producers behind your favourite hip-hop hits \u2013 Livemag|website=livemag.co.za|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> He established his own sole proprietorship Production Company 'Airdee Global'  \"I want to put on as many kids from the Free State on before I die or retire\". Ramolula currently produces and distributes under his own company. Ramolula worked extensively with Chad Da Don and YoungstaCPT on the songs \"F.U\"<ref name=\":0\" /> and \"F.U.2\".<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://skinnygenestv.com/behindtheproducer-airdee-global-on-his-consistent-sound-x-chad-da-don-business-relationship/|title=#BehindTheProducer {{!}} AirDee Global On His Consistent Sound x Chad Da Don Business Relationship \u2013 Skinnygenes.tv|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> In 2018 he released 'Better With Silence' as the lead artist alongside Locnville.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.peoplemagazine.co.za/celebrity-news/locnville-airdee-youngstacpt-join-forces-new-banger-better-silence/|title=Locnville, AirDee and YoungstaCPT Join Forces For New Banger 'Better With Silence'|date=2018-04-03|website=People Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> He reiterated what the collaboration meant to him as he has \"Always been a fan of the homies\", the song also featured YoungstaCPT.Ramolula then worked on YoungstaCPTs' 3T Album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://skinnygenestv.com/behindthealbum-airbreaks-down-his-production-work-on-youngsta-3t-album/|title=BehindTheAlbum {{!}} AirDee Global Breaks Down His Production Work On Youngsta 3T Album \u2013 Skinnygenes.tv|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> Ramolula  produced a piano heavy  'Rare Intro' on the Zoocci Coke Dope and Die Mondez collaborative EP 'Die Dope'.<ref name=\":2\" /> Ramolula would then produce Sheba on Manu Worldstar's 'Young African Story' EP.<ref name=\":6\" /> Ramolula's last production effort of the decade was 'Run' by Free State rap duo StinoLeThwenny.<ref name=\":3\" /> \n<br />\n[[File:Ramolula_with_Kid_X_and_Chad_Da_Don.png|thumb|Ramolula with Kid X and Chad Da Don in 2019]]\n\n== Musical Style ==\nRamolula has described his sound as an influence of 'Lesenke' which is south-sotho word for corrugated iron. It is Kwaito influenced rhythm that brings a timeless element to the current Hip Hop sound. He also has strong command over the piano as can be heard throughout his output. The word Lesenke is also used to refer to Cassette tapes or classical music.\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== 2014 ===\n{{Discography|Name=DJ Capital - Imma Tell Her (featuring. Psyfo and KidX|Other info=produced with Psyfo|Released=2014}}<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.yomzansi.com/2014/03/28/new-music-dj-capital-ft-kid-x-and-psyfo-imma-tell-her/|title=NEW MUSIC : DJ Capital ft Kid X and Psyfo - Imma Tell Her {{!}} YoMZansi|last=tumza7gp|date=2014-03-28|website=www.yomzansi.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>{{Discography|Name=[[iFani]] - Milli|Released=2014|From Album=I Believes In Me|from Album=I Believes In Me}}{{Discography|Name=Notshi - We Don't Care|Released=2014}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slikouronlife.co.za/blog/12039/notshi-we-dont-care|title=Music: Notshi - We Don't Care|website=www.slikouronlife.co.za|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015 ===\n{{Discography|Name=DJ Vigilante - Sorry Makhe (featuring. Yanga, [[L-Tido]] and Kid X|Released=2015}}<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://rarolae.com/new-video-djvigilantesa-ft-team_ltido-kidxoficial-maggz_za-itsyangachief-sorry-makhe/|title=NEW VIDEO: @DJVigilanteSA Ft. @Team_Ltido , @KidXoficial , @Maggz_ZA & @ItsYangaChief \u2013 Sorry Makhe|date=2014-11-25|website=Rarolae.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>{{Discography|Name=Money Nyce - Wildin' Out|Released=2015}}{{Discography|Released 2015|Name=[[Nadia Nakai]] - Whatever (featuring. DotCom and Psyfo)}}{{Discography|Name=AirDee - Hakuna Mathata(featuring. The Fraternity , Junior De Rocka and K2)|Released=2015}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slikouronlife.co.za/blog/1347/stream-and-download-airdee-ft-the-fraternity-k2-and-dj-junior-de-rocka|title=Stream And Download @AirDeeGlobal ft @TheFraternityZA, K_Toozle and @JuniorDeRocka Akuna Mathata|website=www.slikouronlife.co.za|language=en|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>\n\n=== 